al\nelectric field at the junction region. Due to the small bandgap of the\nmaterial, we observe photocurrents and photovoltages for illumination\nwavelengths up to 940 nm, attractive for energy harvesting applications in the\nnear-infrared region\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 10 Jul 2014 16:55:47 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 15 Jul 2014 13:53:34 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Tue, 23 Sep 2014 10:32:01 GMT"}],"update_date":"2014-09-24"}
