 point between the normal semiconducting\n($x < 3%$) and topological semiconducting phases ($x > 3%$) and the time\nreversal symmetry breaking perturbation causes the Dirac point to split into a\npair of Weyl points along the direction of the applied magnetic field for such\na strong spin-orbit coupled system. In this review article, we discuss how the\ntopological structure of both the Berry curvature and chiral anomaly (axion\nelectrodynamics) gives rise to anomalous transport phenomena in\nBi$_{1-x}$Sb$_{x}$ around $x \\sim 3%$ under magnetic fields, modifying the\nDrude model of Landau's Fermi liquids.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 11 Jul 2014 07:37:06 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 13 Oct 2014 05:08:32 GMT"}],"update_date":"2014-11-27"}
