o show that in the settling accretion theory,\nbright X-ray flares (10^{38}-10^{40} ergs) observed in SFXT may be produced by\nsporadic capture of magnetized stellar-wind plasma. At sufficiently low\naccretion rates, magnetic reconnection can enhance the magnetospheric plasma\nentry rate, resulting in copious production of X-ray photons, strong Compton\ncooling and ultimately in unstable accretion of the entire shell. A bright\nflare develops on the free-fall time scale in the shell, and the typical energy\nreleased in an SFXT bright flare corresponds to the mass of the shell.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 11 Jul 2014 14:02:31 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 14 Jul 2014 08:22:57 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-07-16"}
